criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Elderly person with 60 years of age or older;

          -  Diagnosis of mild or major neurocognitive disorder, performed by a physician
             specialized in neurology or psychiatry, or who is validated by the family physician in
             accordance with DSMIII/IV/5 or ICD-9/10 criteria;

          -  Presence of mild to moderate cognitive impairment according to the 6-Item Cognitive
             Decline Test (6CIT);

          -  Capable of communicating and understanding communication;

          -  Without a physical illness or significant disability (eg elderly people who are on
             dialysis or bedridden);

          -  Living in the community (in their home);

          -  Have an informal caregiver available and able to develop the individual cognitive
             stimulation program.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Elderly / informal caregiver with a history of severe psychiatric illness diagnosed
             before 60 years of age;

          -  Informal caregiver with cognitive impairment, even if mild (mild PNC according to
             DSM-5 criteria);

          -  Elderly people who do not live in their home.
